# Natural water, containing [[dissolved]] minerals, which has been treated in any of several ways (filtering, aerating, [[carbonating]] etc) before being [[bottle]]d; used either therapeutically or out of preference. Natural and artificial water with hich concentration of [[sodium bicarbonate]] is also called [[soda water]], where the original [[selters water]] (or [[seltzer]] water) is a German brand in [[generic]] use. 

====Synonyms====
Natural mineral water is a protected label, but some words occur in practical/colloquial use with regional differences
* [[Selters water]] or [[seltzer water]] from the original soda water from the wells in Selters, Germany, or imitated.
* [[seltzer]] (US English), using the name of the original mineral water, but often made without soda salts
* [[soda water]] genuine soda water is mineral water, but not all mineral waters contain much soda. In daily speech little difference is made
* [[carbonated]] water, [[sparkling water]], [[fizzy]] water in the case that salt content is low (colloquial use)

